    <div class="content">
        <img src=""C:\Users\Lenovo\OneDrive\Desktop\ppt\download.jpeg"" alt="Steve Jobs">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>Steve Jobs, born on February 24, 1955, was an American business magnate, industrial designer, and inventor.
            He co-founded Apple Inc., revolutionizing the world of personal computers, smartphones, music, and animated
            films. His visionary leadership and relentless pursuit of excellence have left an indelible mark on the
            technology industry and beyond.</p>

        <h2>Innovation and Vision</h2>
        <p>Steve Jobs was renowned for his unparalleled innovation and visionary thinking. He possessed an innate
            ability to identify groundbreaking ideas and transform them into elegant, user-friendly products. His
            emphasis on design, simplicity, and seamless integration between hardware and software elevated Apple's
            products to new heights.</p>

        <h2>Apple Inc.</h2>
        <p>As the co-founder of Apple Inc., Steve Jobs played a pivotal role in the company's success. He introduced
            iconic products such as the Macintosh, iPod, iPhone, and iPad, which revolutionized their respective
            industries and transformed Apple into one of the most valuable and influential companies in the world.
            Under his leadership, Apple became synonymous with innovation, quality, and exceptional user experience.</p>

        <h2>Legacy and Impact</h2>
        <p>Steve Jobs' impact extended far beyond the realm of technology. His relentless pursuit of perfection,
            ability to inspire others, and refusal to accept the status quo continue to inspire countless individuals
            around the world. His legacy serves as a reminder that passion, determination, and a commitment to excellence
            can reshape industries and change the world.</p>

        <blockquote class="quote">
            "Your work is going to fill a large part of your life, and the only way to be truly satisfied is to do what you
            believe is great work. And the only way to do great work is to love what you do." - Steve Jobs
        </blockquote>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>Steve Jobs' contributions as an innovator, entrepreneur, and visionary have left an indelible impact on
            society. His relentless pursuit of excellence, passion for design, and transformative products continue to
            shape the way we live, work, and interact with technology.</p>
